cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and generative models for learning feature hierarchies, which are common topics in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses variational methods and disentangled features, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
